CatDescriptText: Jacqueline (Jacky) Cobb, registered nurse, 36 Elmore Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 12, 1957, pg. 2 with question: "Do you think the Little Rock, Ark. school integration incident will gain more financial support for the NAACP in its continuing fight for equal rights?"  Answer reads: "I think it will, because you can see that you are fighting for a group of young people (in Little Rock) and not just for one individual."
